# label: BUGGY (stale with parity_check)
# role: agent tool — known-deliberate Go↔Elm divergences

Companion to `parity_check.py`. Holds per-pair lists of
exports that exist on one side but not the other
DELIBERATELY — so parity_check can subtract them before
reporting drift.

## Rule for entries

Each IGNORE entry gets a short comment explaining WHY it's
deliberate. This file doubles as the "why we chose to
diverge" record for future-us. Do NOT silence drift without
understanding it.

## Status (FIRM)

Co-stale with `parity_check.py` — the pair names may still
be correct, but the whole tool is blocked on the stale
`GO_ROOT` / `ELM_ROOT` paths in `parity_check.py`. Once that's
fixed, audit this file: any entries referring to names from
before the reorg may no longer be accurate.

## Pointers

- Consumer: `parity_check.py`.
